 Orange Democratic Movement (ODM) party leader
Raila Odinga is on Friday expected to hold his 77th birthday
celebrations in Nairobi. The celebration, according to a statement
from ODM Director of Communications Philip Etale, will happen at the Bomas
of Kenya. Odinga will be joined by family members as
well as several invited dignitaries to mark the occasion.  According to Etale, the celebration will run
from 9am to 12pm.